TITLE: Using the useParty Hook in a React Component
DESCRIPTION: Example of how to use the useParty hook to access the party context in a React component. It demonstrates submitting mutations and handling party state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/threepointone/partyserver/blob/main/docs/guides/multi-parties.md#2025-04-15_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useParty } from '@partyserver/sdk'

export default function Counter() {
  // get the party
  const party = useParty()

  async function onClick() {
    // submit a mutation to the party
    await party.mutate('increment')
  }

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{party.state.counter}</h1>
      <button onClick={onClick}>increment</button>
    </div>
  )
}
```

