TITLE: Creating a WebSocket Server with Party Protocol Support
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to create a WebSocket server with Party protocol support, which enables communication with multiple clients. Demonstrates handling connections, registering with a lobby, and managing state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/threepointone/partyserver/blob/main/docs/guides/rpc.md#2025-04-15_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { partyserver } from 'partyserver'

const server = partyserver()

server.party({
  onConnect(channel, socket) {
    console.log(`${socket.id} connected to ${channel}!`)

    // broadcast to all other clients in this channel
    socket.broadcast('user-joined', { id: socket.id })

    // send to just this client
    socket.send('welcome', { message: 'hello!' })

    // share state with the lobby
    socket.lobby.register('users', socket.id, { name: 'sunil' })

    // get some state
    const users = socket.lobby.get('users')

    // on message from client
    socket.on('message', (type, data) => {
      if (type === 'rename') {
        socket.lobby.register('users', socket.id, { name: data.name })
      }
    })

    // on close
    socket.on('close', () => {
      socket.lobby.unregister('users', socket.id)
      socket.broadcast('user-left', { id: socket.id })
    })
  }
})
```

