TITLE: Creating a TypeScript Party Configuration
DESCRIPTION: TypeScript implementation for configuring Party Server types and handlers. Defines the State interface and handler functions for increment and decrement operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/threepointone/partyserver/blob/main/docs/guides/multi-parties.md#2025-04-15_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// party.ts

import { Party } from '@partyserver/sdk/server'

export interface State {
  counter: number
}

const party = new Party<State>()

// initialize the state
party.init(() => ({
  counter: 0,
}))

// define handlers for mutations
party.mutation('increment', ({ state }) => {
  state.counter += 1
})

party.mutation('decrement', ({ state }) => {
  state.counter -= 1
})

export default party
```

